    .entry-details
      %p.desc
        %strong> Description:
        Set one or more CSS properties for the  set of matched elements.
      %ul.signatures
        %li#css-propertyName-value.signature
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.0/"} 1.0
            \.css( propertyName, value )
          %p.arguement
            %strong> propertyName
            A CSS property name.
          %p.arguement
            %strong> value
            A value to set for the property.
        %li.signature{:id => "css-propertyName-functionindex, value"}
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.4/"} 1.4
            \.css( propertyName, function(index, value) )
          %p.arguement
            %strong> propertyName
            A CSS property name.
          %p.arguement
            %strong> function(index, value)
            A function returning the value to set. Receives the index position of the element in the set and the old value as arguments.
        %li#css-map.signature
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.0/"} 1.0
            \.css( map )
          %p.arguement
            %strong> map
            A map of property-value pairs to set.
      .longdesc
        %p
          As with the
          %code .attr()
          method, the
          %code .css()
          method makes setting properties of elements quick and easy. This method can take either a property name and value as separate parameters, or a single map of key-value pairs (JavaScript object notation).
        %p
          Also, jQuery can equally interpret the CSS and DOM formatting of multiple-word properties. For example, jQuery understands and returns the correct value for both
          %code .css({'background-color': '#ffe', 'border-left': '5px solid #ccc'})
          and
          = succeed "." do
            %code .css({backgroundColor: '#ffe', borderLeft: '5px solid #ccc'})
          Notice that with the DOM notation, quotation marks around the property names are optional, but with CSS notation they're required due to the hyphen in the name.
        %p
          As with
          = succeed "," do
            %code
              %a{:href => "/attr"} .attr()
          %code .css()
          allows us to pass a function as the property value:
        %pre
          :preserve
            $('div.example').css('width', function(index) {
              return index * 50;
            });        %p This example sets the widths of the matched elements to incrementally larger values.
      %h3 Examples:
      #entry-examples.entry-examples
        #example-0
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc To change the color of any paragraph to red on mouseover event.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  p { color:blue; width:200px; font-size:14px; }
                  &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	
                  &lt;p&gt;Just roll the mouse over me.&lt;/p&gt;
                
                  &lt;p&gt;Or me to see a color change.&lt;/p&gt;
                  
                &lt;script&gt;
                  $("p").mouseover(function () {
                    $(this).css("color","red");
                  });
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
        #example-1
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc To highlight a clicked word in the paragraph.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  p { color:blue; font-weight:bold; cursor:pointer; }
                  &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	
                &lt;p&gt;
                  Once upon a time there was a man
                  who lived in a pizza parlor. This
                  man just loved pizza and ate it all 
                  the time.  He went on to be the
                  happiest man in the world.  The end.
                &lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;script&gt;
                  var words = $("p:first").text().split(" ");
                  var text = words.join("&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;");
                  $("p:first").html("&lt;span&gt;" + text + "&lt;/span&gt;");
                  $("span").click(function () {
                    $(this).css("background-color","yellow");
                  });
                
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
        #example-2
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc To set the color of all paragraphs to red and background to blue:
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  p { color:green; }
                &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	
                  &lt;p&gt;Move the mouse over a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
                  &lt;p&gt;Like this one or the one above.&lt;/p&gt;
                
                &lt;script&gt;
                  $("p").hover(function () {
                    $(this).css({'background-color' : 'yellow', 'font-weight' : 'bolder'});
                  }, function () {
                    var cssObj = {
                      'background-color' : '#ddd',
                      'font-weight' : '',
                      'color' : 'rgb(0,40,244)'
                    }
                    $(this).css(cssObj);
                  });
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
        #example-3
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc Increase the size of a div when you click it:
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  div { width: 20px; height: 15px; background-color: #f33; }
                  &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	
                  &lt;div&gt;click&lt;/div&gt;
                  &lt;div&gt;click&lt;/div&gt;
                
                &lt;script&gt;
                  $("div").click(function() {
                    $(this).css({
                      width: function(index, value) {
                        return parseFloat(value) * 1.2;
                      }, 
                      height: function(index, value) {
                        return parseFloat(value) * 1.2;
                      }
                
                    });
                  });
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
